{
  "pattern": {
    "summary": "Fold an outer floating-point compare through a select when the select is guarded by an fcmp over the same two values chosen by the select, and the guard predicate is commutative or otherwise safe for the matched-arm configuration.",
    "generalized_ir_shape": [
      "%c = fcmp <pred1> Ty %a, %b",
      "%s = select i1 %c, Ty %t, Ty %f",
      "%r = fcmp <pred2> Ty %s, %k"
    ],
    "preconditions": [
      "The select arms %t and %f are exactly the two operands of the guarding fcmp, in either order: {%t,%f} = {%a,%b}.",
      "The transformation is valid when the guard fcmp predicate is commutative for the encountered arm/operand match configuration; notably this includes predicates like oeq and une, and avoids bailing out solely because operands match in swapped order.",
      "The outer compare must be simplifiable because under the guard, selecting between the two compared values preserves the needed semantics. A key motivating case is guarding with 'ord %x, C0' and selecting between %x and C0, then comparing the result against a constant C1.",
      "NaN behavior must be preserved. The fold is justified because the select condition already constrains which arm is chosen, and for commutative guard predicates the swapped-arm form is equivalent."
    ],
    "canonical_example": {
      "before": [
        "%c = fcmp ord double %x, 0.0",
        "%s = select i1 %c, double %x, double 0.0",
        "%r = fcmp oeq double %s, 1.0"
      ],
      "after": [
        "%r = fcmp oeq double %x, 1.0"
      ]
    },
    "implementation_note": "In FoldOpIntoSelect(), when the select condition is an FCmpInst and the select true/false values are the same two operands used by that fcmp, do not reject the fold merely because the operands match in swapped order if the guarding fcmp predicate is commutative. Only preserve the bailout for non-commutative predicates where operand direction matters.",
    "covered_forms": [
      "select arms in the same order as the guard fcmp operands",
      "select arms in swapped order relative to the guard fcmp operands",
      "variable/constant and constant/variable operand arrangements",
      "ordered and unordered outer comparisons, provided NaN semantics remain implied by the guard"
    ]
  },
